    "body": "**<sub><sub>![P2 Badge](https://img.shields.io/badge/P2-yellow?style=flat)</sub></sub>  Detect all required shell tools before unskipping script tests**\n\nThe new skip gate only checks `os.name != \"nt\"` and `bash` presence, but `scripts/package_release.sh` also hard-depends on `python3` and `sha256sum` (see its invocations at lines 6, 16, 23, and 26). On environments like macOS or minimal POSIX images where `bash` exists but `sha256sum` does not, these tests will run and fail instead of being skipped, which contradicts the stated goal of skipping when required POSIX tooling is unavailable. Please include checks for all required executables (or skip on non-Linux) in the gating condition.\n\nUseful? React with 👍 / 👎.",
